In my email today:
From: The Honorable Dana Rohrabacher
Date: 4/27/2012
EPA Compromises the Integrity of Science 
Dear Colleague:
‚ÄúWhich do you find more shocking: that the Environmental Protection Agency conducts experiments on humans that its own risk assessment would deem potentially lethal, or that it hides the results of those experiments from Congress and the public because they debunk those very same assessments?‚Äù 
This critical question forms the basis for the attached Washington Times article: ‚ÄúDid Obama‚Äôs EPA relaunch Tuskegee experiments?‚Äù By Steve Milloy.
Moreover, this is one more piece of evidence that EPA uses science to play games, manipulate data, and generate faulty outcomes to justify their regulations. Here is a compelling example that highlights faulty science: ‚ÄúEPA researchers who conducted the experiments published the case study of the 58-year woman in the government journal Environmental Health Perspectives in which they casually disregard the woman‚Äôs preexisting conditions and blame her atrial fibrillation on PM2.2. They also failed to disclose the existence- let alone the results ‚Äì of the other 40 experiments.‚Äù
If you are interested in understanding how the EPA continues to compromise the integrity of science, please read the full article here: http://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2012/apr/24/did-obamas-epa-relaunch-tuskegee-experiments/.
In Freedom,
/s/
Dana Rohrabacher
Member of Congress
=================================================================
I suppose next, the EPA will try to shut down the Volcanoes National Park because it is ‚Äútoo dangerous‚Äù.



